Former law clerks of Supreme Court nominee Neil Gorsuch have signed a letter to the Senate Judiciary Committee praising his independence. They emphasize Gorsuch's adherence to the Constitution and the rule of law, stating that he never decides cases based on personal views or desires. The former clerks highlight Gorsuch's willingness to take principled positions even if he stands alone. They express confidence that his independence will remain steadfast if he is confirmed as a Supreme Court Justice.